description.narrative: UNICEF used the COVID19 pandemic to innovate, build new partnerships and accelerate such WASH programming opportunities as WASH in institutions (health facilities and schools) and promotion of handwashing with water and soap. UNICEF's earlier investments in the Ebola preparedness and response activities, WASH in institutions, and upstream support to the Ministry of Water and Environment and the Ministry of Health helped to effectively engage in the government coordination and response structures and reorient UNICEF support to the most pressing areas. Donor support through UNICEF (US$1.7 million) and some private sector initiatives have been key in supporting the Government. | Status:No Progress | As-of Date:30/07/2020
